{
  "texts": [
    "A more tightly integrated strategy involves enabling the LLM to interact directly with a Language Server.",
    "For example, the RATester framework pauses upon encountering an unfamiliar identifier during code generation to query the language server for its definition.",
    "It then dynamically injects this new information back into the prompt, thereby enriching the context in real-time and mitigating hallucinations [157].Recent research has materialized this concept into autonomous test agents.",
    "TestForge [69] serves as a prominent example, equipped with a suite of tools for interacting with code repositories, such as editing files, executing tests, and retrieving coverage data.",
    "Beyond simple execution loops, agents are evolving to perform strategic, multi-step test planning."
  ]
}